# ✅ Code Review Checklist

Before marking any implementation as complete, verify:

## Functionality

- [ ] Code implements the requested feature completely
- [ ] All edge cases are handled
- [ ] Error handling is implemented
- [ ] Input validation is in place

## Testing

- [ ] Tests follow the project structure convention
- [ ] Tests cover happy path scenarios
- [ ] Tests cover error cases
- [ ] Tests cover edge cases
- [ ] Test names are descriptive
- [ ] Tests are independent and can run in any order

## Code Quality

- [ ] Code follows Django best practices
- [ ] No duplicate code or logic
- [ ] Existing model methods are reused
- [ ] Imports are organized correctly
- [ ] Code is readable and well-commented
- [ ] No hardcoded values (use constants or config)

## Models

- [ ] Model fields are appropriate for data types
- [ ] Relationships are properly defined
- [ ] Model methods are utilized when available
- [ ] Database migrations are created if needed

## Documentation

- [ ] Functions have docstrings
- [ ] Complex logic is commented
- [ ] README is updated if needed

## Security

- [ ] No sensitive data in code
- [ ] Input is validated and sanitized
- [ ] Authentication/authorization is checked
- [ ] SQL injection prevention (use ORM)

## Performance

- [ ] No N+1 queries
- [ ] Appropriate use of select_related/prefetch_related
- [ ] Database indexes considered for frequent queries
